;; **
;;; ### Application Conditions
;;; 
;;; Rules may be required to meet certain conditions to be applicable. These so-called _application conditions_ include conditions that are global to a rule's matching semantics and conditions that pertain to individual graph elements (local application conditions). 
;;; 
;;; #### Global application conditions
;;; 
;;; ##### Injectivity condition
;;; Rules may be defined to require **_injective_** matching semantics. By default, different graph elements in the rule are allowed to match to the _same_ graph element in the graph that the rule is applied to. To understand this better, consider a graph (`g1`) with one `Hello` node:
;; **

;; @@
(def g1 (-> (newgrape) hello))
(view g1)
